The '''2014 All-Ireland Intermediate Hurling Championship''' was the 31st staging of the All-Ireland [[hurling]] championship for players in the intermediate grade since its establishment by the [[Gaelic Athletic Association]] in 1961. The championship began on 25 May 2014 and ended on 9 August 2014.

[[Tipperary GAA|Tipperary]] were the [[2013 All-Ireland Intermediate Hurling Championship|defending champions]], however, they were defeated in the provincial decider.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.irishexaminer.com/archives/2013/0902/ireland/tipp-shake-off-plucky-cats-241717.html|title=Tipp shake off plucky Cats |publisher=Irish Independent|date=2 September 2013|accessdate=1 May 2014|first=John|last=Knox}}</ref> [[Cork GAA|Cork]] won the title after defeating [[Wexford GAA|Wexford]] by 2-18 to 2-12 in the All-Ireland final.

